## Task-Type Specific Criteria

### For "implement" Tasks
- [ ] Feature works as specified
- [ ] No regressions in existing functionality
- [ ] Configuration updated if needed
- [ ] Examples provided if applicable

### For "fix" Tasks
- [ ] Bug is resolved
- [ ] Root cause addressed (not just symptoms)
- [ ] Fix verified with test case
- [ ] No new issues introduced

### For "refactor" Tasks
- [ ] Behavior preserved (no functional changes)
- [ ] Code is cleaner/more maintainable
- [ ] Tests still pass
- [ ] Performance not degraded

### For "analyze" Tasks
- [ ] Analysis is thorough and accurate
- [ ] Findings are documented
- [ ] Recommendations are actionable
- [ ] Sources/references cited

### For "organize" Tasks
- [ ] Organization is logical and consistent
- [ ] All items properly categorized
- [ ] No items lost or duplicated
- [ ] Documentation reflects new structure

